  "title": "Transport Controller #76541",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Industry/ Organization Type: Logistics</li><li>Position Title: <strong>Transport Controller</strong></li><li>Working Location: Jurong East</li><li>Working Hours: 5.5 days (Mon – Fri, 830am – 530pm; Sat, 830am - 1230pm)</li><li>Salary Package: <strong>Basic salary up to $5,000 + Variable Bonus</strong></li><li>Duration: Permanent Role</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Oversee the daily scheduling and dispatch of vehicles to ensure optimal routing and resource utilization</li><li>Plan and monitor routes, taking into account traffic, delivery timelines, and operational efficiency</li><li>Coordinate and communicate with drivers, ensuring clear instructions and prompt response to any issues</li><li>Enforce compliance with all relevant transport and safety regulations, including escort requirements and PSA (Port of Singapore Authority) regulations</li><li>Supervise fleet management activities including vehicle maintenance schedules, inspections, and documentation</li><li>Manage and resolve logistical challenges, delays, or emergencies in a timely and effective manner</li><li>Handle customer inquiries regarding transport and delivery, providing accurate updates and solutions</li><li>Maintain accurate records of fleet operations, incident reports, and regulatory compliance</li><li>Liaise with regulatory authorities and ensure all transport activities meet industry standards and company policies</li><li>Ensure all drivers and transport staff receive training on safety, compliance, and customer service</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>APPLY NOW!!!</strong></p><ul><li>Proven experience in fleet management, logistics coordination, or a related transportation role</li><li>Strong knowledge of escort operations, PSA regulations, and relevant transport legislation in Singapore</li><li>Good communication and interpersonal skills to work effectively with drivers, regulatory authorities, and customers</li><li>Proficient in transport management systems and route planning software</li><li></li></ul><p>Kindly apply through <strong>ANY </strong>of the following methods:</p><ul><li>Submit your application by clicking the <strong>APPLY </strong>button;</li><li>Email your resume to <a href=\"mailto:Job@anradus.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Job@anradus.com.sg</a>. Please indicate <strong>#76541 </strong>on the email subject.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Anradus Application Policy:</strong> We value each application and ensure every resume is reviewed. Our process is efficient, typically concluding within <strong>3 working days</strong>. If you do not receive communication from us within this timeframe, it's likely that your application has not been shortlisted by our client. In such cases, we recommend continuing your job search to maximize your opportunities.</p><p><br /><br /></p><p>Anradus Pte Ltd | EA License No. 20C0161 | Rachael Lee | EA Reg No.: R2093131</p>",
